A '''cruciferous vegetable''' or a '''crucifer''' refers to a member of the plant family Brassicaceae. The family is also known as Cruciferae.<ref name="wp">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cruciferous_vegetables</ref> This latter alternative name alludes to the cross shape of the flowers, which have four petals shaped like a cross.

The most well known cruciferous plant types grown in the garden and crop context include:
*[[Broccoli]]
*[[Brussels sprouts]]
*[[Cabbage]]
*[[Cauliflower]]
*[[Collards]]
*[[Kale]]
*[[Mustard]]
*[[Radishes]]
*[[Turnips]].

